    "actor_description": "Heat rushes up my face before I can get ahead of it, like my skin is tattling on me. My thoughts stutter—too aware of my hands, my voice, the space I'm taking—and I want to shrink without actually disappearing. I try to smooth it over fast, but the more I try to look normal, the more obvious it feels. It's not crushing—just sharp, bright, and inconvenient.",
